text: Soloneshensky District () is an administrativeLaw #28-ZS and municipalLaw #83-ZS district (raion), one of the fifty-nine in Altai Krai, Russia. It is located in the southeast of the krai. The area of the district is . Its administrative center is the rural locality (a selo) of Soloneshnoye. Population: The population of Soloneshnoye accounts for 41.4% of the district's total population. ==See also== * Okladnikov Cave * Denisova Cave ==References== ===Notes=== ===Sources=== * * Category:Districts of Altai Krai
